<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Challenge 2: Cookie Monster</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Challenges</a>
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="EECS Girls Who Tech Camp" class="page-logo">

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>🍪 Challenge 2: Cookie Monster</h1>
      <p class="desc">A mystery shop hid a secret in your browser's "cookies." Can you find it?</p>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <div class="story-box">
        Websites can secretly stash little pieces of data in your browser — they're called <strong>cookies</strong>. This shop put several cookies in your browser. One of them contains the flag!
      </div>

      <div class="fake-website">
        <div class="fake-navbar">
          <span>🏪 The Mystery Shop</span>
          <span>Home | Products | Contact</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fake-body">
          <h2>Welcome to The Mystery Shop!</h2>
          <p>I've secretly placed some "cookies" in your browser. 🍪🍪🍪</p>
          <p>There are several cookies, but only ONE has the real flag!</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tools-section">
        <h3>🛠️ How to peek at cookies</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Press <code>F12</code> → go to <code>Application</code> tab → click <code>Cookies</code></li>
          <li>Or type <code>document.cookie</code> in the Console tab</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="hint-box">
        <details>
          <summary class="hint-toggle">💡 Need a hint?</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;">Look for a cookie named <code>secret_flag</code>. The other two are decoys!</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flag-form">
      <input type="text" class="flag-input" id="flagInput" placeholder="flag{...}" />
      <button class="submit-btn" onclick="submitFlag('ch2')">Submit Flag</button>
    </div>
    <div class="result-msg" id="result"></div>
  </div>
  <script src="/js/submit.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
